On Mon, 18 Jan 1999, Erik Corry wrote:
> Yes, but above the refresh rate of your monitor, so how come you can
> see it?
AFAIK linux assignes multiple timeslices to processes. If a process runs
for 20 timeslices that is already 0.2 sec. Have multiple of those and
things lag badly.
